      "side": 1,
      "message": "There are two related packages:\n - github.com/jcgregorio/slog defines an interface for a logging impl\n - github.com/jcgregorio/logger implements the interface with a logger that can write to stderr or not at all\n\nThis package is an adapter for github.com/jcgregorio/slog, but also has LogMode and NewStdErr to make it easy to instantiate an Adapter pointing to github.com/jcgregorio/logger.\n\nI figured I should keep slog working since it\u0027s already used in our repo. But if you prefer, it should be easy to replace it with a simple stdout implementation.",
